def: One of the suckerlike rootlets of such plants as the dodder andivy. R. Brown.
The pin, or gnomon, of a dial, the shadow of which indicatesthe hour. See Gnomon. (f) Etym: [Probably fr. Gr. (Bot.)
Between the mandibles; interramal; as, the intermandibularspace.

A strong metallic vessel, usually of wrought iron platesriveted together, or a composite structure variously formed, in whichsteam is generated for driving engines, or for heating, cooking, orother purposes.
A quadrangle or court, as of a prison; hence, a prison. [Slang]"Flogged or whipped in quod." T. Hughes.
A deal at cards that draws all the tricks. Swift.
To make womanish; to make soft and delicate; to weaken.It will not corrupt or effeminate children's minds. Locke.
